<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-10-10T07:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-10-10T07:00:00-05:00" n="515" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d515">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">300.115/14401: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Consul General at London</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Skinner</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-10-10T12:00:00+00:00"><hi rend="italic">October
                                            10, 1918—12 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received October
                                    11—6:21 p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                            <p>Department’s 4th, mine, September 28, 12 noon. … Proposal extends
                                only to goods or proceeds on list. Status of remittances different
                                    <pb facs="0711" n="621" xml:id="pg_621"/> from goods in that
                                title thereto has passed to enemy addressees. This status described
                                in my despatch 6719 dated September 5th, 1918, subject George
                                    Dohrmann.<note n="20" xml:id="d515fn20">Not printed.</note> Am
                                endeavoring to arrange with British authorities for return to
                                American claimants of the deposits in Prize Court equivalent to
                                total invoice value of the goods in whatever goods were not
                                contraband and title thereto can be proven to be in American
                                claimants.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Skinner</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>